---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words Ending in -RY — From ARCHERY to JEWELRY"
  description="Top Scrabble words ending in -RY with point breakdowns. JEWELRY 20pts, HICKORY 19pts, ARCHERY 15pts. Complete -RY suffix word list for competitive Scrabble strategy."
  keywords="scrabble words ending in ry, jewelry scrabble points, hickory scrabble, archery scrabble word, ry ending words, high scoring ry words scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words Ending in -RY — From ARCHERY to JEWELRY","description":"Top Scrabble words ending in -RY with point breakdowns. JEWELRY 20pts, HICKORY 19pts, ARCHERY 15pts.","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-ending-in-ry"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"How many points is JEWELRY worth in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"JEWELRY scores 20 points in Scrabble (J=8, E=1, W=4, E=1, L=1, R=1, Y=4). The J tile alone contributes 8 points, making this one of the highest-scoring -RY words available."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is HICKORY a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! HICKORY scores 19 points (H=4, I=1, C=3, K=5, O=1, R=1, Y=4) and is valid in both major dictionaries. As a 7-letter word, it qualifies for the 50-point bingo bonus."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What are the best -RY words for Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Top -RY words include JEWELRY (20pts), HICKORY (19pts), MOCKERY (18pts), ARCHERY (15pts), and BRAVERY (15pts). The -RY ending adds 5 points (R=1, Y=4), with high scores coming from premium letters in the root."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words Ending in -RY — From ARCHERY to JEWELRY</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">The -RY suffix is one of the most versatile in Scrabble. It forms nouns (BAKERY, BRAVERY), adjectives (WINTRY, HUNGRY), and appears in hundreds of valid words. The R contributes just 1 point, but Y adds 4 — and the real scoring comes from premium letters in the root word like J, K, W, and H.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">20 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">JEWELRY (Top)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">19 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">HICKORY</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">18 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">MOCKERY</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">15 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">ARCHERY</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Highest-Scoring -RY Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">JEWELRY — 20 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">J=8, E=1, W=4, E=1, L=1, R=1, Y=4 · 7 letters · Bingo candidate</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">JEWELRY combines the J tile (8pts) with W (4pts) and Y (4pts) for a 20-point base. As a 7-letter word, it qualifies for the 50-point bingo bonus — a potential 70-point single play.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🌳 HICKORY</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">19 pts · H=4, I=1, C=3, K=5, O=1, R=1, Y=4 · K tile powerhouse</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">😤 MOCKERY</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">18 pts · M=3, O=1, C=3, K=5, E=1, R=1, Y=4 · K + C combo</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🏹 ARCHERY</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">15 pts · A=1, R=1, C=3, H=4, E=1, R=1, Y=4 · Common tiles</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⚔️ BRAVERY</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">15 pts · B=3, R=1, A=1, V=4, E=1, R=1, Y=4 · V tile value</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Solid Mid-Range -RY Plays</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">BAKERY</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">15pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">WINTRY</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">12pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">PANTRY</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">11pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">QUARRY</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">18pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">HUNGRY</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">13pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">POETRY</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">11pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for -RY Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">7-letter -RY words are bingo gold:</span> JEWELRY, HICKORY, ARCHERY, BRAVERY, MOCKERY — all 7 letters. Hold R and Y together and build toward these bingos for 50-point bonuses.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Hook existing words:</span> JEWEL→JEWELRY, ARCHER→ARCHERY, BRAVE→BRAVERY. If the root is already on the board, extend it with RY to score the full word again plus parallels.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Short -RY for tight spots:</span> DRY (7pts), FRY (9pts), TRY (6pts), CRY (8pts), and PRY (8pts) are compact 3-letter plays that fit anywhere on a crowded board.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">The -RY suffix is <span class="text-white font-medium">the best bingo-forming ending</span> for words containing K, J, or W. These premium consonants rarely appear in other 7-letter-friendly suffixes, making -RY your go-to when holding these tiles.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find every valid -RY word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
      <!-- Related Articles -->
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-700 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-ending-in-tion/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words Ending in -TION</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-ending-in-ize/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words Ending in -IZE</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-ending-in-ny/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words Ending in -NY</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-ending-in-ly/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words Ending in -LY</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-ending-in-ment/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words Ending in -MENT</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
